title: Judicial vacancies in Lower 48 at both the Appelate and District courts, USA, 1999 and 2007
name: Judicial vacancies in Lower 48 at both the Appelate and District courts, USA, 1999 and 2007
description: The map is based on Judgeship vacancies data from the U.S. Courts (http://www.uscourts.gov/cfapps/webnovada/CF_FB_301/index.cfm?fuseaction=Reports.ViewSummary)It shows judicial vacancies for both Clinton and Bush for the comparable time periods (Aug, 1999 and Aug, 2007). Clinton adminstration and Republican dominated congress were haggling over how to fill  61 judicial vacancies. While today Bush adminstration and Congress dominated by Democrats are tied over 50 judicial vacancies.
